Through this course, you will learn:
• human information processing theory (in depth) and human performance in complex tasks;
• measures of human cognitive states, including situation awareness and workload;
• how to conduct (cognitive) task analyses;
• application of cognitive task analysis in usability evaluation and interface design;
• how to develop user models to describe human performance and optimize complex system interface design;
• a wide range of cognitive performance modeling techniques including KLM, GOMS, CPM-GOMS, NGOMSL, ACT-R, EPIC, QN-MHP, and their applications in different domains (e.g., in-vehicle information systems, assistive technology)
